info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 11 at 11:11AM CST until January 11 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Heavy lake effect snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to 4 inches. * WHERE...Southern Lake County. * WHEN...Until 9 PM CST this evening. * IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous conditions could impact the evening commute. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The greatest snow totals will be found in the higher elevation areas from near Silver Bay to Finland to Murphy City northeastward to the Cook County line.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.
